Usipii ac Tencteri] According to caesar, these tribes being expelled from their abodes by the Suevi. after three years' wandering seized the lande of the Menapii, between the Rhine and the Moselle. After their conquest by Caesar, the survivors took refuge amongst the Sugambri, and on the removal of the latter to Gaul, occupied their scats near the Luppia (Lippe). Afterwards the Usi - pii moved South between the Sieg and the Lahn: the Tencteri settled between the Sieg and the Ruhr.
